================================================================================
Third-party components
================================================================================

Strop's own source is GPL-3.0-or-later. The compiled application links a large
tree of third-party crates; the great majority are permissively licensed (MIT,
Apache-2.0, BSD, ISC, Zlib, Unicode-3.0). The items worth calling out:

gpui, gpui_platform, gpui_wgpu  —  Apache-2.0
    The UI framework, from Zed Industries
    (https://github.com/zed-industries/zed). `vendor/gpui_wgpu/` is a copy of
    Zed's gpui_wgpu carrying a single local modification (a per-glyph swash
    ScaleContext, working around an upstream Wayland scale-change glyph
    rasterization bug — see docs/UPSTREAM-gpui-scale-bug.md).

zlog, ztracing, ztracing_macro  —  GPL-3.0-or-later
    Pulled in transitively through gpui -> sum_tree. Because these are linked
    into the binary, the assembled Strop application is GPL-3.0-or-later as a
    whole. (This is the same situation as the Zed editor itself.)

PT Serif, PT Sans, PT Mono  —  SIL Open Font License 1.1
    Copyright (C) ParaType. Bundled in assets/fonts/; license text in
    assets/fonts/PTSerif-OFL.txt, PTSans-OFL.txt, and PTMono-OFL.txt.

URW Bookman  —  AGPL-3.0 with font-embedding exception
    Copyright (C) 2015 URW Software; 2013, 2014 (URW)++ Design & Development
    (the urw-base35 set, https://github.com/ArtifexSoftware/urw-base35-fonts).
    The cold read's book face, shipped as RUNTIME DATA FILES in
    assets/fonts/coldread/ (read at startup, never compiled into the
    binary); full license text beside the fonts in
    assets/fonts/coldread/LICENSE. AGPLv3 and GPLv3 are one-way compatible
    (each license's §13), and the fonts remain independent works on disk.

Hyphenation pattern data (runtime data files, assets/hyphenation/):
  en-us.standard.bincode  —  Copyright (C) 1990, 2004, 2005 Gerard D.C.
    Kuiken. "Copying and distribution of this file, with or without
    modification, are permitted in any medium without royalty provided the
    copyright notice and this notice are preserved."
  ru.standard.bincode  —  Copyright (C) 1999-2003 Alexander I. Lebedev,
    LPPL 1.2-or-later (the ruhyphen patterns). The LPPL is GPL-incompatible,
    which is why this dictionary ships as a loose runtime file and is never
    embedded in the binary.
    Both compiled from hyph-utf8 (https://www.hyphenation.org/tex) via the
    `hyphenation` crate v0.8.4; full notices in
    assets/hyphenation/ATTRIBUTION.txt.

ropey (MIT), loro (MIT), pulldown-cmark (MIT), image (MIT OR Apache-2.0),
hyphenation (Apache-2.0 OR MIT), and the remaining direct dependencies are
permissively licensed.

A complete, machine-generated per-crate license inventory can be produced with
`cargo about generate`, or inspected with `cargo deny list`.
